//Design a 4-bit adder.
//There are two 4 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The adder should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to determine the output sum and cout.
//Please finish the module.

module adder(output [3:0] sum, output cout, input [3:0] in1, in2, input cin);

wire c1, c2, c3;

full_adder FA1(sum[0], c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);
full_adder FA2(sum[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
full_adder FA3(sum[2], c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);
full_adder FA4(sum[3], cout, in1[3], in2[3], c3);

endmodule

//Design a 4-bit adder.
//There are two 4 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The adder should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to determine the output sum and cout.
//Please finish the module.

module adder(output [3:0] sum, output cout, input [3:0] in1, in2, input cin);

wire c1, c2, c3;

full_adder FA1(sum[0], c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);
full_adder FA2(sum[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
full_adder FA3(sum[2], c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);
full_adder FA4(sum[3], cout, in1[3], in2[3], c3);

endmodule

module full_adder(output sum, output cout, input in1, in2, cin);

wire x, y, z;

xor(sum, in1, in2, cin);
and(x, in1, in2);
and(y, in1, cin);
and(z, in2, cin);
or(cout, x, y, z);

endmodule

xor(sum, in1, in2, cin);

//Design a 4-bit adder.
//There are two 4 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The adder should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to determine the output sum and cout.
//Please finish the module.

module adder(output [3:0] sum, output cout, input [3:0] in1, in2, input cin);

	wire [3:0] sum;
	wire cout;
	wire [3:0] in1;
	wire [3:0] in2;
	wire cin;

	assign sum = in1 + in2 + cin;
	assign cout = (in1[3] & in2[3] & cin) | (in1[3] & cin) | (in2[3] & cin) | (cin & in1[3] & in2[3]);

endmodule

//Design a 4-bit adder.
//There are two 4 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The adder should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to determine the output sum and cout.
//Please finish the module.

module adder(output [3:0] sum, output cout, input [3:0] in1, in2, input cin);
	wire [3:0] carry;
	
	fa_adder fa_adder_0(sum[0], carry[0], in1[0], in2[0], cin);
	fa_adder fa_adder_1(sum[1], carry[1], in1[1], in2[1], carry[0]);
	fa_adder fa_adder_2(sum[2], carry[2], in1[2], in2[2], carry[1]);

//Design a 4-bit adder.
//There are two 4 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The adder should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to determine the output sum and cout.
//Please finish the module.

module adder(output [3:0] sum, output cout, input [3:0] in1, in2, input cin);
	wire [3:0] carry;
	
	fa_adder fa_adder_0(sum[0], carry[0], in1[0], in2[0], cin);
	fa_adder fa_adder_1(sum[1], carry[1], in1[1], in2[1], carry[0]);
	fa_adder fa_adder_2(sum[2], carry[2], in1[2], in2[2], carry[1]);
	fa_adder fa_adder_3(sum[3], cout, in1[3], in2[3], carry[2]);
	
endmodule

module fa_adder(output sum, carry, input a, b, cin);
	wire [3:0] carry_temp;
	
	fa_adder fa_adder_0(sum[0], carry_temp[0], a, b, cin);
	fa_adder fa_adder_1(sum[1], carry_temp[1], carry_temp[0], a, b);
	fa_adder fa_adder_2(sum[2], carry_temp[2], carry_temp[1], carry_temp[0], a);
	fa_adder fa_adder_3(sum[3], carry, carry_temp[2], carry_temp[1], carry_temp[0]);
	
endmodule

//Design a 4-bit adder.
//There are two 4 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The adder should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to determine the output sum and cout.
//Please finish the module.

module adder(output [3:0] sum, output cout, input [3:0] in1, in2, input cin);   

wire c1, c2, c3;

full_adder FA1(sum[0], c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);
full_adder FA2(sum[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
full_adder FA3(sum[2], c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);
full_adder FA4(sum[3], cout, in1[3], in2[3], c3);

endmodule

module full_adder(output sum, carry, input a, b, cin);

wire x, y, z;

xor(sum, a, b, cin);
and(x, a, b);
and(y, b, cin);
and(z, a, cin);
or(carry, x, y, z);

endmodule

//Design a 4-bit adder.
//There are two 4 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The adder should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to determine the output sum and cout.
//Please finish the module.

module adder(output [3:0] sum, output cout, input [3:0] in1, in2, input cin);

	wire [3:0] sum;
	wire cout;
	wire [3:0] in1;
	wire [3:0] in2;
	wire cin;

	assign sum = in1 + in2 + cin;
	assign cout = (in1[3] & in2[3] & cin) | (in1[3] & cin) | (in2[3] & cin) | (cin & in1[3] & in2[3]);

endmodule

//Design a 4-bit adder.
//There are two 4 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The adder should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to determine the output sum and cout.
//Please finish the module.

module adder(output [3:0] sum, output cout, input [3:0] in1, in2, input cin);   

wire c1, c2, c3;

full_adder FA1(sum[0], c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);
full_adder FA2(sum[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);

endmodule

module full_adder(output sum, carry, input a, b, cin);

wire x, y, z;

xor(sum, a, b, cin);
and(x, a, b);
and(y, b, cin);
and(z, a, cin);
or(carry, x, y, z);

endmodule

module full_adder(output sum, carry, input a, b, cin);

wire x, y, z;

xor(sum, a, b, cin);
and(x, a, b);
and(y, b, cin);
and(z, a, cin);
or(carry, x, y, z);

endmodule

//Design a 4-bit adder.
//There are two 4 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The adder should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to determine the output sum and cout.
//Please finish the module.

module adder(output [3:0] sum, output cout, input [3:0] in1, in2, input cin);
    wire [3:0] sum;
    wire cout;
    wire [3:0] in1;
    wire [3:0] in2;
    wire cin;
    
    assign sum = in1 + in2 + cin;
    assign cout = (in1[3] & in2[3] & cin) | (in1[3] & cin) | (in2[3] & cin) | (cin & in1[3] & in2[3]);

endmodule

	fa_adder fa_adder_0(sum[0], carry[0], in1[0], in2[0], cin);

module fa_adder(output sum, carry, input a, b, cin);
	wire [3:0] carry_temp;
	
	fa_adder fa_adder_0(sum[0], carry_temp[0], a, b, cin);
	fa_adder fa_adder_1(sum[1], carry_temp[1], carry_temp[0], a, b);
	fa_adder fa_adder_2(sum[2], carry_temp[2], carry_temp[1], carry_temp[0], a);
	fa_adder fa_adder_3(sum[3], carry, carry_temp[2], carry_temp[1], carry_temp[0]);
	
endmodule

//The adder should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to determine the output sum and cout.
//Please finish the module.

module adder(output [3:0] sum, output cout, input [3:0] in1, in2, input cin);

wire c1, c2, c3;

full_adder FA1(sum[0], c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);
full_adder FA2(sum[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
full_adder FA3(sum[2], c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);
full_adder FA4(sum[3], cout, in1[3], in2[3], c3);

endmodule

module full_adder(output sum, output cout, input in1, in2, cin);

wire x, y, z;

xor(sum, in1, in2, cin);
and(x, in1, in2);
and(y, in1, cin);
and(z, in2, cin);
or(cout, x, y, z);

endmodule

//Design a 4-bit adder.
//There are two 4 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The adder should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to determine the output sum and cout.

	wire [3:0] carry;
	
	fa_adder fa_adder_0(sum[0], carry[0], in1[0], in2[0], cin);
	fa_adder fa_adder_1(sum[1], carry[1], in1[1], in2[1], carry[0]);
	fa_adder fa_adder_2(sum[2], carry[2], in1[2], in2[2], carry[1]);

//Design a 4-bit adder.
//There are two 4 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The adder should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to determine the output sum and cout.
//Please finish the module.

module adder(output [3:0] sum, output cout, input [3:0] in1, in2, input cin);
	wire [3:0] carry;
	
	fa_adder fa_adder_0(sum[0], carry[0], in1[0], in2[0], cin);
	fa_adder fa_adder_1(sum[1], carry[1], in1[1], in2[1], carry[0]);
	fa_adder fa_adder_2(sum[2], carry[2], in1[2], in2[2], carry[1]);
	fa_adder fa_adder_3(sum[3], cout, in1[3], in2[3], carry[2]);
	
endmodule

module fa_adder(output sum, carry, input a, b, cin);
	wire [3:0] carry_temp;
	
	fa_adder fa_adder_0(sum[0], carry_temp[0], a, b, cin);
	fa_adder fa_adder_1(sum[1], carry_temp[1], carry_temp[0], a, b);
	fa_adder fa_adder_2(sum[2], carry_temp[2], carry_temp[1], carry_temp[0], a);
	fa_adder fa_adder_3(sum[3], carry, carry_temp[2], carry_temp[1], carry_temp[0]);
	
endmodule

//Design a 4-bit adder.
//There are two 4 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The adder should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to determine the output sum and cout.
//Please finish the module.

module adder(output [3:0] sum, output cout, input [3:0] in1, in2, input cin);

	wire [3:0] sum;
	wire cout;
	wire [3:0] in1;
	wire [3:0] in2;
	wire cin;

	assign sum = in1 + in2 + cin;
	assign cout = (in1[3] & in2[3] & cin) | (in1[3] & cin) | (in2[3] & cin) | (cin & in1[3] & in2[3]);

endmodule

//Design a 4-bit adder.
//There are two 4 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.

//Design a 4-bit adder.
//There are two 4 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The adder should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to determine the output sum and cout.
//Please finish the module.

module adder(output [3:0] sum, output cout, input [3:0] in1, in2, input cin);

	wire c1, c2, c3;

	full_adder FA1(sum[0], c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);
	full_adder FA2(sum[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
	full_adder FA3(sum[2], c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);
	full_adder FA4(sum[3], cout, in1[3], in2[3], c3);

endmodule

module full_adder(output sum, output cout, input in1, in2, cin);

	wire x, y, z;

	xor(sum, in1, in2, cin);
	and(x, in1, in2);
	and(y, in1, cin);
	and(z, in2, cin);
	or(cout, x, y, z);

endmodule

module full_adder(output sum, output cout, input in1, in2, cin);

	wire x, y, z;

	xor(sum, in1, in2, cin);
	and(x, in1, in2);
	and(y, in1, cin);
	and(z, in2, cin);
	or(cout, x, y, z);

endmodule

//Design a 4-bit adder.
//There are two 4 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The adder should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to determine the output sum and cout.
//Please finish the module.

module adder(output [3:0] sum, output cout, input [3:0] in1, in2, input cin);

	wire [3:0] sum;
	wire cout;
	wire [3:0] in1;
	wire [3:0] in2;
	wire cin;

	assign sum = in1 + in2 + cin;
	assign cout = (in1[3] & in2[3] & cin) | (in1[3] & cin) | (in2[3] & cin) | (cin & in1[3] & in2[3]);

endmodule

//Design a 4-bit adder.
//There are two 4 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The adder should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to determine the output sum and cout.
//Please finish the module.

module adder(output [3:0] sum, output cout, input [3:0] in1, in2, input cin);

wire [3:0] c;

assign c[0] = cin;

full_adder FA0(sum[0], c[1], in1[0], in2[0], c[0]);
full_adder FA1(sum[1], c[2], in1[1], in2[1], c[1]);
full_adder FA2(sum[2], c[3], in1[2], in2[2], c[2]);

//Design a 4-bit adder.
//There are two 4 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.

module adder(output [3:0] sum, output cout, input [3:0] in1, in2, input cin);

assign c[0] = cin;

full_adder FA0(sum[0], c[1], in1[0], in2[0], c[0]);

module full_adder(output sum, output cout, input in1, in2, cin);

wire x, y, z;

xor(sum, in1, in2, cin);
and(x, in1, in2);
and(y, in1, cin);
and(z, in2, cin);
or(cout, x, y, z);

endmodule

module fa_adder(output sum, carry, input a, b, cin);

wire c1, c2, c3;

xor(sum, a, b, cin);
and(c1, a, b);
and(c2, b, cin);
and(c3, a, cin);
or(carry, c1, c2, c3);

endmodule

module adder(output [3:0] sum, output cout, input [3:0] in1, in2, input cin);

wire c1, c2, c3;

full_adder FA1(sum[0], c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);
full_adder FA2(sum[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
full_adder FA3(sum[2], c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);
full_adder FA4(sum[3], cout, in1[3], in2[3], c3);

endmodule

module full_adder(output sum, output cout, input in1, in2, cin);

wire x, y, z;

xor(sum, in1, in2, cin);
and(x, in1, in2);
and(y, in1, cin);
and(z, in2, cin);
or(cout, x, y, z);

endmodule

module full_adder(output sum,carry,input a,b,cin);

wire x,y,z;

xor(sum,a,b,cin);
and(x,a,b);
and(y,b,cin);
and(z,a,cin);
or(carry,x,y,z);

endmodule

//Design a 4-bit adder.
//There are two 4 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The adder should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to determine the output sum and cout.
//Please finish the module.

module adder(output [3:0] sum, output cout, input [3:0] in1, in2, input cin);

wire [3:0] sum;
wire cout;

wire [3:0] in1;
wire [3:0] in2;
wire cin;

assign sum = in1 + in2 + cin;
assign cout = (in1[3] == in2[3] && (in1[3] == cin))? 1'b1 : 1'b0;

endmodule

//Design a 4-bit adder.
//There are two 4 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The adder should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to determine the output sum and cout.
//Please finish the module.

module adder(output [3:0] sum, output cout, input [3:0] in1, in2, input cin);
    wire [3:0] sum;
    wire cout;
    wire [3:0] in1;
    wire [3:0] in2;
    wire cin;
    
    assign sum = in1 + in2 + cin;
    assign cout = (in1[3] & in2[3] & cin) | (in1[3] & cin) | (in2[3] & cin) | (cin & in1[3] & in2[3]);

endmodule

//Design a 4-bit adder.
//There are two 4 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The adder should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to determine the output sum and cout.
//Please finish the module.

module adder(output [3:0] sum, output cout, input [3:0] in1, in2, input cin);

wire [3:0] carry;

fa_adder fa_adder_0(sum[0], carry[0], in1[0], in2[0], cin);
fa_adder fa_adder_1(sum[1], carry[1], in1[1], in2[1], carry[0]);
fa_adder fa_adder_2(sum[2], carry[2], in1[2], in2[2], carry[1]);
fa_adder fa_adder_3(sum[3], cout, in1[3], in2[3], carry[2]);

endmodule

module fa_adder(output sum, carry, input a, b, cin);

wire c1, c2, c3;

xor(sum, a, b, cin);
and(c1, a, b);
and(c2, b, cin);
and(c3, a, cin);
or(carry, c1, c2, c3);

endmodule

xor(sum, in1, in2, cin);

//Design a 4-bit adder.
//There are two 4 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The adder should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to determine the output sum and cout.
//Please finish the module.

module adder(output [3:0] sum, output cout, input [3:0] in1, in2, input cin);

wire [3:0] in1_w, in2_w;
wire cin_w;

assign in1_w = in1;
assign in2_w = in2;
assign cin_w = cin;

full_adder FA0(sum[0], cin_w, in1_w[0], in2_w[0], cin_w);
full_adder FA1(sum[1], cin_w, in1_w[1], in2_w[1], cin_w);
full_adder FA2(sum[2], cin_w, in1_w[2], in2_w[2], cin_w);
full_adder FA3(sum[3], cout, in1_w[3], in2_w[3], cin_w);

endmodule

module full_adder(output sum, output cout, input in1, in2, cin);

wire x, y, z;

xor(sum, in1, in2, cin);
and(x, in1, in2);
and(y, in1, cin);
and(z, in2, cin);
or(cout, x, y, z);

endmodule

//Design a 4-bit adder.
//There are two 4 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The adder should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to determine the output sum and cout.
//Please finish the module.

module adder(output [3:0] sum, output cout, input [3:0] in1, in2, input cin);

wire [3:0] in1_w, in2_w;
wire cin_w;

assign in1_w = in1;
assign in2_w = in2;
assign cin_w = cin;

full_adder FA0(sum[0], cin_w, in1_w[0], in2_w[0], cin_w);
full_adder FA1(sum[1], cin_w, in1_w[1], in2_w[1], cin_w);
full_adder FA2(sum[2], cin_w, in1_w[2], in2_w[2], cin_w);
full_adder FA3(sum[3], cout, in1_w[3], in2_w[3], cin_w);

endmodule

module full_adder(output sum, output cout, input in1, in2, cin);

wire x, y, z;

xor(sum, in1, in2, cin);
and(x, in1, in2);
and(y, in1, cin);
and(z, in2, cin);
or(cout, x, y, z);

endmodule

//Design a 4-bit adder.
//There are two 4 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The adder should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to determine the output sum and cout.

//Design a 4-bit adder.
//There are two 4 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The adder should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to determine the output sum and cout.
//Please finish the module.

module adder(output [3:0] sum, output cout, input [3:0] in1, in2, input cin);

wire [4:0] carry;

fa_adder fa_adder_0(sum[0], carry[0], in1[0], in2[0], cin);
fa_adder fa_adder_1(sum[1], carry[1], in1[1], in2[1], carry[0]);
fa_adder fa_adder_2(sum[2], carry[2], in1[2], in2[2], carry[1]);
fa_adder fa_adder_3(sum[3], cout, in1[3], in2[3], carry[2]);

endmodule

module fa_adder(output sum, carry, input a, b, cin);

wire c1, c2, c3;

xor(sum, a, b, cin);
and(c1, a, b);
and(c2, b, cin);
and(c3, a, cin);
or(carry, c1, c2, c3);

endmodule

//Design a 4-bit adder.
//There are two 4 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The adder should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to determine the output sum and cout.
//Please finish the module.

module adder(output [3:0] sum, output cout, input [3:0] in1, in2, input cin);

wire c1, c2, c3;

full_adder FA1(sum[0], c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);
full_adder FA2(sum[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
full_adder FA3(sum[2], c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);
full_adder FA4(sum[3], cout, in1[3], in2[3], c3);

endmodule

module full_adder(output sum, output cout, input in1, in2, cin);

wire x, y, z;

xor(sum, in1, in2, cin);
and(x, in1, in2);
and(y, in1, cin);
and(z, in2, cin);
or(cout, x, y, z);

endmodule

module full_adder(output sum, carry, input a, b, cin);

wire x, y, z;

xor(sum, a, b, cin);
and(x, a, b);
and(y, b, cin);
and(z, a, cin);
or(carry, x, y, z);

endmodule

//Design a 4-bit adder.
//There are two 4 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The adder should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to determine the output sum and cout.
//Please finish the module.

module adder(output [3:0] sum, output cout, input [3:0] in1, in2, input cin);

wire [3:0] temp1;
wire [3:0] temp2;
wire [3:0] temp3;
wire [3:0] temp4;
wire [3:0] temp5;
wire [3:0] temp6;
wire [3:0] temp7;
wire [3:0] temp8;

assign temp1 = in1 ^ in2;
assign temp2 = in1 & in2;
assign temp3 = in1 | in2;
assign temp4 = in1 ^ in2;

assign temp5 = temp1 ^ temp2;
assign temp6 = temp1 & temp2;
assign temp7 = temp1 | temp2;
assign temp8 = temp1 ^ temp2;

assign sum = temp1 ^ temp3;
assign cout = temp4 ^ temp5 ^ temp6 ^ temp7;

endmodule

//Design a 4-bit adder.
//There are two 4 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The adder should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to determine the output sum and cout.
//Please finish the module.

module adder(output [3:0] sum, output cout, input [3:0] in1, in2, input cin);   
    wire [3:0] sum;
    wire cout;
    wire [3:0] in1;
    wire [3:0] in2;
    wire cin;
    
    assign sum = in1 + in2 + cin;
    assign cout = (in1[3] & in2[3] & cin) | (in1[3] & cin) | (in2[3] & cin) | (cin & in1[3] & in2[3]);

endmodule

//Design a 4-bit adder.
//There are two 4 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The adder should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to determine the output sum and cout.
//Please finish the module.

//Design a 4-bit adder.
//There are two 4 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The adder should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to determine the output sum and cout.
//Please finish the module.

module adder(output [3:0] sum, output cout, input [3:0] in1, in2, input cin);

wire c1, c2, c3;

full_adder FA1(sum[0], c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);
full_adder FA2(sum[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
full_adder FA3(sum[2], c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);
full_adder FA4(sum[3], cout, in1[3], in2[3], c3);

endmodule

//There are two 4 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The adder should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to determine the output sum and cout.

module full_adder(output sum, output cout, input in1, in2, cin);

wire x, y, z;

xor(sum, in1, in2, cin);
and(x, in1, in2);
and(y, in1, cin);
and(z, in2, cin);
or(cout, x, y, z);

endmodule

module full_adder(output sum,carry,input a,b,cin);

wire x,y,z;

xor(sum,a,b,cin);
and(x,a,b);
and(y,b,cin);
and(z,a,cin);
or(carry,x,y,z);

endmodule

//Design a 4-bit adder.
//There are two 4 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The adder should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to determine the output sum and cout.
//Please finish the module.

module adder(output [3:0] sum, output cout, input [3:0] in1, in2, input cin);   

	wire [3:0] sum;
	wire cout;
	wire [3:0] in1;
	wire [3:0] in2;
	wire cin;

	assign sum = in1 + in2 + cin;
	assign cout = (in1[3] & in2[3] & cin) | (in1[3] & cin) | (in2[3] & cin) | (cin & in1[3] & in2[3]);

endmodule

//Design a 4-bit adder.
//There are two 4 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The adder should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to determine the output sum and cout.
//Please finish the module.

module adder(output [3:0] sum, output cout, input [3:0] in1, in2, input cin);

reg [3:0] sum;
reg cout;

always @(in1 or in2 or cin)
begin
	sum = in1 + in2 + cin;
	cout = (in1[0] & in2[0] & cin) | (in1[0] & in2[0] & ~cin) | (in1[0] & ~cin & ~in2[0]) | (~in1[0] & ~in2[0] & cin);
end

endmodule

module full_adder(output sum, output cout, input in1, in2, cin);

wire x, y, z;

xor(sum, in1, in2, cin);
and(x, in1, in2);
and(y, in1, cin);
and(z, in2, cin);
or(cout, x, y, z);

endmodule

//Design a 4-bit adder.
//There are two 4 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.

module full_adder(output sum, output cout, input in1, in2, input cin);
wire w1, w2, w3;

xor(w1, in1, in2);
xor(sum, w1, cin);
and(w2, w1, cin);
and(w3, in1, in2);
or(cout, w2, w3);

endmodule

//Design a 4-bit adder.
//There are two 4 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The adder should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to determine the output sum and cout.
//Please finish the module.

module adder(output [3:0] sum, output cout, input [3:0] in1, in2, input cin);
wire [3:0] in1_w, in2_w;
wire cin_w;

assign in1_w = in1;
assign in2_w = in2;
assign cin_w = cin;

full_adder FA1(sum[0], in1_w[0], in2_w[0], cin_w, cout_w);
full_adder FA2(sum[1], in1_w[1], in2_w[1], cout_w, cout_w);
full_adder FA3(sum[2], in1_w[2], in2_w[2], cout_w, cout_w);
full_adder FA4(sum[3], in1_w[3], in2_w[3], cout_w, cout_w);

endmodule

full_adder FA2(sum[1], in1_w[1], in2_w[1], cout_w, cout_w);
full_adder FA3(sum[2], in1_w[2], in2_w[2], cout_w, cout_w);
full_adder FA4(sum[3], in1_w[3], in2_w[3], cout_w, cout_w);

module full_adder(output sum, output cout, input in1, in2, input cin);
wire w1, w2, w3;

xor(w1, in1, in2);
xor(sum, w1, cin);
and(w2, w1, cin);
and(w3, in1, in2);
or(cout, w2, w3);

endmodule

//Design a 4-bit adder.
//There are two 4 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The adder should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to determine the output sum and cout.
//Please finish the module.

module adder(output [3:0] sum, output cout, input [3:0] in1, in2, input cin);
wire [3:0] in1_w, in2_w;
wire cin_w;

assign in1_w = in1;
assign in2_w = in2;
assign cin_w = cin;

full_adder FA1(sum[0], in1_w[0], in2_w[0], cin_w, cout_w);
full_adder FA2(sum[1], in1_w[1], in2_w[1], cout_w, cout_w);
full_adder FA3(sum[2], in1_w[2], in2_w[2], cout_w, cout_w);
full_adder FA4(sum[3], in1_w[3], in2_w[3], cout_w, cout_w);

endmodule

module full_adder(output sum, output cout, input in1, in2, input cin);
wire w1, w2, w3;

xor(w1, in1, in2);
xor(sum, w1, cin);
and(w2, w1, cin);
and(w3, in1, in2);
or(cout, w2, w3);

endmodule

module full_adder(output sum, output cout, input in1, in2, cin);
wire x, y, z;

xor(sum, in1, in2, cin);
and(x, in1, in2);
and(y, in1, cin);
and(z, in2, cin);
or(cout, x, y, z);

//There are two 4 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.

//Design a 4-bit adder.
//There are two 4 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The adder should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to determine the output sum and cout.
//Please finish the module.

module adder(output [3:0] sum, output cout, input [3:0] in1, in2, input cin);
wire [3:0] in1_w, in2_w;
wire cin_w;

assign in1_w = in1;
assign in2_w = in2;
assign cin_w = cin;

full_adder FA1(sum[0], in1_w[0], in2_w[0], cin_w, cout_w);
full_adder FA2(sum[1], in1_w[1], in2_w[1], cout_w, cout_w);
full_adder FA3(sum[2], in1_w[2], in2_w[2], cout_w, cout_w);
full_adder FA4(sum[3], in1_w[3], in2_w[3], cout_w, cout_w);

endmodule

wire cin_w;

assign in1_w = in1;
assign in2_w = in2;
assign cin_w = cin;

module full_adder(output sum, output cout, input in1, in2, input cin);
wire w1, w2, w3;

xor(w1, in1, in2);
xor(sum, w1, cin);
and(w2, w1, cin);
and(w3, in1, in2);
or(cout, w2, w3);

endmodule

//Design a 4-bit adder.
//There are two 4 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The adder should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to determine the output sum and cout.
//Please finish the module.

module adder(output [3:0] sum, output cout, input [3:0] in1, in2, input cin);
wire [3:0] in1;
wire [3:0] in2;
wire cin;

assign sum = in1 + in2 + cin;
assign cout = (in1[3] == in2[3])? 0 : (in1[3] == cin? 1 : in1[3] + in2[3] + cin);

endmodule

//Design a 4-bit adder.
//There are two 4 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The adder should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to determine the output sum and cout.
//Please finish the module.

module adder(output [3:0] sum, output cout, input [3:0] in1, in2, input cin);
wire [3:0] in1_w, in2_w;
wire cin_w;

assign in1_w = in1;
assign in2_w = in2;
assign cin_w = cin;

full_adder FA1(sum[0], in1_w[0], in2_w[0], cin_w, cout_w);
full_adder FA2(sum[1], in1_w[1], in2_w[1], cout_w, cout_w);
full_adder FA3(sum[2], in1_w[2], in2_w[2], cout_w, cout_w);
full_adder FA4(sum[3], in1_w[3], in2_w[3], cout_w, cout_w);

module full_adder(output sum, output cout, input in1, in2, input cin);
wire w1, w2, w3;

and(w3, in1, in2);
or(cout, w2, w3);

module full_adder(output sum, output cout, input in1, in2, cin);
wire x, y, z;

xor(sum, in1, in2, cin);
and(x, in1, in2);
and(y, in1, cin);
and(z, in2, cin);
or(cout, x, y, z);

endmodule

//Design a 4-bit adder.
//There are two 4 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The adder should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to determine the output sum and cout.
//Please finish the module.

module adder(output [3:0] sum, output cout, input [3:0] in1, in2, input cin);
wire [4:0] carry;

fa fa0(sum[0], carry[0], in1[0], in2[0], cin);
fa fa1(sum[1], carry[1], in1[1], in2[1], carry[0]);
fa fa2(sum[2], carry[2], in1[2], in2[2], carry[1]);
fa fa3(sum[3], cout, in1[3], in2[3], carry[2]);

//Design a 4-bit adder.
//There are two 4 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The adder should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to determine the output sum and cout.
//Please finish the module.

module adder(output [3:0] sum, output cout, input [3:0] in1, in2, input cin);
wire [4:0] carry;

fa fa0(sum[0], carry[0], in1[0], in2[0], cin);
fa fa1(sum[1], carry[1], in1[1], in2[1], carry[0]);
fa fa2(sum[2], carry[2], in1[2], in2[2], carry[1]);
fa fa3(sum[3], cout, in1[3], in2[3], carry[2]);

endmodule

module fa(output sum, output cout, input a, b, cin);
wire c1, c2, c3;

xor(sum, a, b, cin);
and(c1, a, b);
and(c2, b, cin);
and(c3, a, cin);
or(cout, c1, c2, c3);

endmodule

//There are two 4 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.

module full_adder(output sum, output cout, input in1, in2, input cin);
wire w1, w2, w3;

xor(w1, in1, in2);
xor(sum, w1, cin);
and(w2, w1, cin);
and(w3, in1, in2);
or(cout, w2, w3);

endmodule

//Design a 4-bit adder.
//There are two 4 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The adder should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to determine the output sum and cout.
//Please finish the module.

module adder(output [3:0] sum, output cout, input [3:0] in1, in2, input cin);
wire [3:0] in1_w, in2_w;
wire cin_w;

assign in1_w = in1;
assign in2_w = in2;
assign cin_w = cin;

full_adder FA1(sum[0], in1_w[0], in2_w[0], cin_w, cout_w);
full_adder FA2(sum[1], in1_w[1], in2_w[1], cout_w, cout_w);
full_adder FA3(sum[2], in1_w[2], in2_w[2], cout_w, cout_w);
full_adder FA4(sum[3], in1_w[3], in2_w[3], cout_w, cout_w);

endmodule

full_adder FA4(sum[3], in1_w[3], in2_w[3], cout_w, cout_w);

module full_adder(output sum, output cout, input in1, in2, input cin);
wire w1, w2, w3;

xor(w1, in1, in2);
xor(sum, w1, cin);
and(w2, w1, cin);
and(w3, in1, in2);
or(cout, w2, w3);

endmodule

//Design a 4-bit adder.
//There are two 4 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The adder should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to determine the output sum and cout.
//Please finish the module.

module adder(output [3:0] sum, output cout, input [3:0] in1, in2, input cin);
wire [3:0] in1_w, in2_w;
wire cin_w;

assign in1_w = in1;
assign in2_w = in2;
assign cin_w = cin;

full_adder FA1(sum[0], in1_w[0], in2_w[0], cin_w, cout_w);
full_adder FA2(sum[1], in1_w[1], in2_w[1], cout_w, cout_w);
full_adder FA3(sum[2], in1_w[2], in2_w[2], cout_w, cout_w);
full_adder FA4(sum[3], in1_w[3], in2_w[3], cout_w, cout_w);

endmodule

module full_adder(output sum, output cout, input in1, in2, input cin);
wire w1, w2, w3;

xor(w1, in1, in2);
xor(sum, w1, cin);
and(w2, w1, cin);
and(w3, in1, in2);
or(cout, w2, w3);

endmodule

//There are two 4 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The adder should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to determine the output sum and cout.
//Please finish the module.

wire cin_w;

assign cin_w = cin;

module full_adder(output sum, output cout, input in1, in2, input cin);
wire w1, w2, w3;

xor(w1, in1, in2);
xor(sum, w1, cin);
and(w2, w1, cin);
and(w3, in1, in2);
or(cout, w2, w3);

//Design a 4-bit adder.
//There are two 4 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The adder should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to determine the output sum and cout.
//Please finish the module.

module adder(output [3:0] sum, output cout, input [3:0] in1, in2, input cin);
wire [3:0] in1_w, in2_w;
wire cin_w;

assign in1_w = in1;
assign in2_w = in2;
assign cin_w = cin;

full_adder FA1(sum[0], in1_w[0], in2_w[0], cin_w, cout_w);
full_adder FA2(sum[1], in1_w[1], in2_w[1], cout_w, cout_w);
full_adder FA3(sum[2], in1_w[2], in2_w[2], cout_w, cout_w);

module full_adder(output sum, output cout, input in1, in2, input cin);
wire w1, w2, w3;

xor(w1, in1, in2);
xor(sum, w1, cin);
and(w2, w1, cin);
and(w3, in1, in2);
or(cout, w2, w3);

//Design a 4-bit adder.
//There are two 4 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The adder should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to determine the output sum and cout.
//Please finish the module.

module adder(output [3:0] sum, output cout, input [3:0] in1, in2, input cin);
wire [3:0] in1_w, in2_w;
wire cin_w;

assign in1_w = in1;
assign in2_w = in2;
assign cin_w = cin;

full_adder FA1(sum[0], in1_w[0], in2_w[0], cin_w, cout_w);
full_adder FA2(sum[1], in1_w[1], in2_w[1], cout_w, cout_w);
full_adder FA3(sum[2], in1_w[2], in2_w[2], cout_w, cout_w);
full_adder FA4(sum[3], in1_w[3], in2_w[3], cout_w, cout_w);

endmodule

wire cin_w;

assign in2_w = in2;
assign cin_w = cin;

module full_adder(output sum, output cout, input in1, in2, input cin);
wire w1, w2, w3;

xor(w1, in1, in2);
xor(sum, w1, cin);
and(w2, w1, cin);
and(w3, in1, in2);
or(cout, w2, w3);

endmodule

module full_adder(output sum, output cout, input in1, in2, cin);
wire x, y, z;

xor(sum, in1, in2, cin);
and(x, in1, in2);
and(y, in1, cin);
and(z, in2, cin);
or(cout, x, y, z);

endmodule

//Design a 4-bit adder.
//There are two 4 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The adder should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to determine the output sum and cout.
//Please finish the module.

module adder(output [3:0] sum, output cout, input [3:0] in1, in2, input cin);
wire [3:0] in1_w, in2_w;
wire cin_w;

assign in1_w = in1;
assign in2_w = in2;
assign cin_w = cin;

full_adder FA1(sum[0], in1_w[0], in2_w[0], cin_w, cout_w);
full_adder FA2(sum[1], in1_w[1], in2_w[1], cout_w, cout_w);
full_adder FA3(sum[2], in1_w[2], in2_w[2], cout_w, cout_w);
full_adder FA4(sum[3], in1_w[3], in2_w[3], cout_w, cout_w);

endmodule

module full_adder(output sum, output cout, input in1, in2, input cin);
wire w1, w2, w3;

xor(w1, in1, in2);
xor(sum, w1, cin);
and(w2, w1, cin);
and(w3, in1, in2);
or(cout, w2, w3);

endmodule

//Design a 4-bit adder.
//There are two 4 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The adder should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to determine the output sum and cout.
//Please finish the module.

module adder(output [3:0] sum, output cout, input [3:0] in1, in2, input cin);
wire [3:0] in1_w, in2_w;
wire cin_w;

assign in1_w = in1;
assign in2_w = in2;
assign cin_w = cin;

full_adder FA1(sum[0], in1_w[0], in2_w[0], cin_w, cout_w);
full_adder FA2(sum[1], in1_w[1], in2_w[1], cout_w, cout_w);
full_adder FA3(sum[2], in1_w[2], in2_w[2], cout_w, cout_w);
full_adder FA4(sum[3], in1_w[3], in2_w[3], cout_w, cout_w);

endmodule

//Design a 4-bit adder.
//There are two 4 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The adder should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to determine the output sum and cout.
//Please finish the module.

module adder(output [3:0] sum, output cout, input [3:0] in1, in2, input cin);
wire [3:0] in1_w, in2_w;
wire cin_w;

assign in1_w = in1;
assign in2_w = in2;
assign cin_w = cin;

full_adder FA1(sum[0], in1_w[0], in2_w[0], cin_w, cout_w);
full_adder FA2(sum[1], in1_w[1], in2_w[1], cout_w, cout_w);
full_adder FA3(sum[2], in1_w[2], in2_w[2], cout_w, cout_w);
full_adder FA4(sum[3], in1_w[3], in2_w[3], cout_w, cout_w);

endmodule

module full_adder(output sum, output cout, input in1, in2, input cin);
wire w1, w2, w3;

xor(w1, in1, in2);
xor(sum, w1, cin);
and(w2, w1, cin);
and(w3, in1, in2);
or(cout, w2, w3);

endmodule

endmodule

xor(w1, in1, in2);

and(w3, in1, in2);

//Design a 4-bit adder.
//There are two 4 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The adder should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to determine the output sum and cout.
//Please finish the module.

module adder(output [3:0] sum, output cout, input [3:0] in1, in2, input cin);
wire [3:0] in1_w, in2_w;
wire cin_w;

assign in1_w = {in1[3], in1[2], in1[1], in1[0]};
assign in2_w = {in2[3], in2[2], in2[1], in2[0]};
assign cin_w = cin;

full_adder FA1(sum[0], c1, in1_w[0], in2_w[0], cin_w);
full_adder FA2(sum[1], c2, in1_w[1], in2_w[1], c1);
full_adder FA3(sum[2], c3, in1_w[2], in2_w[2], c2);
full_adder FA4(sum[3], cout, in1_w[3], in2_w[3], c3);

endmodule

module full_adder(output sum, carry, input a, b, cin);
wire w1, w2, w3;

xor(w1, a, b);
xor(sum, w1, cin);
and(w2, w1, cin);
and(w3, a, b);
or(carry, w2, w3);

endmodule

wire cout_w;

assign in1_w = in1;
assign in2_w = in2;
assign cin_w = cin;

full_adder FA1(sum_w[0], c1, in1_w[0], in2_w[0], cin_w);
full_adder FA2(sum_w[1], c2, in1_w[1], in2_w[1], c1);
full_adder FA3(sum_w[2], c3, in1_w[2], in2_w[2], c2);
full_adder FA4(sum_w[3], cout_w, in1_w[3], in2_w[3], c3);

assign sum = sum_w;
assign cout = cout_w;

endmodule

//Design a 4-bit adder.
//There are two 4 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The adder should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to determine the output sum and cout.
//Please finish the module.

module adder(output [3:0] sum, output cout, input [3:0] in1, in2, input cin);
wire [3:0] in1_w, in2_w;
wire cin_w;

assign in1_w = in1;
assign in2_w = in2;
assign cin_w = cin;

//Design a 4-bit adder.
//There are two 4 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The adder should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to determine the output sum and cout.
//Please finish the module.

module adder(output [3:0] sum, output cout, input [3:0] in1, in2, input cin);
wire [3:0] in1_w;
wire [3:0] in2_w;
wire cin_w;

assign in1_w = in1;
assign in2_w = in2;
assign cin_w = cin;

full_adder FA1(sum[0], c1, in1_w[0], in2_w[0], cin_w);
full_adder FA2(sum[1], c2, in1_w[1], in2_w[1], c1);
full_adder FA3(sum[2], c3, in1_w[2], in2_w[2], c2);
full_adder FA4(sum[3], cout, in1_w[3], in2_w[3], c3);

endmodule

//Please finish the module.

module adder(output [3:0] sum, output cout, input [3:0] in1, in2, input cin);
wire [3:0] in1_w;
wire [3:0] in2_w;
wire cin_w;

assign in2_w = in2;
assign cin_w = cin;

full_adder FA1(sum[0], c1, in1_w[0], in2_w[0], cin_w);

module full_adder(output sum, output cout, input in1, in2, input cin);
wire w1, w2, w3;

xor(w1, in1, in2);
xor(sum, w1, cin);
and(w2, w1, cin);
and(w3, in1, in2);
or(cout, w2, w3);

endmodule

//Design a 4-bit adder.
//There are two 4 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.

module fa(output sum, output cout, input a, b, cin);
wire c1, c2, c3;

xor(sum, a, b, cin);
and(c1, a, b);
and(c2, b, cin);
and(c3, a, cin);
or(cout, c1, c2, c3);

endmodule

module full_adder(output sum, output cout, input in1, in2, cin);
wire x, y, z;

xor(sum, in1, in2, cin);
and(x, in1, in2);
and(y, in1, cin);
and(z, in2, cin);
or(cout, x, y, z);

endmodule

//Design a 4-bit adder.
//There are two 4 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The adder should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to determine the output sum and cout.
//Please finish the module.

module adder(output [3:0] sum, output cout, input [3:0] in1, in2, input cin);
wire [3:0] in1;
wire [3:0] in2;
wire cin;

assign sum = in1 + in2 + cin;
assign cout = (in1[3] == in2[3])? 0 : (in1[3] == cin? 1 : in1[3] + in2[3] + cin);

endmodule

//Design a 4-bit adder.
//There are two 4 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The adder should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to determine the output sum and cout.
//Please finish the module.

module adder(output [3:0] sum, output cout, input [3:0] in1, in2, input cin);
wire [3:0] in1_wire, in2_wire;
wire cin_wire;

assign in1_wire = in1;
assign in2_wire = in2;
assign cin_wire = cin;

full_adder FA1(sum[0], in1_wire[0], in2_wire[0], cin_wire, cout_wire);
full_adder FA2(sum[1], in1_wire[1], in2_wire[1], cout_wire, cout_wire);
full_adder FA3(sum[2], in1_wire[2], in2_wire[2], cout_wire, cout_wire);
full_adder FA4(sum[3], in1_wire[3], in2_wire[3], cout_wire, cout_wire);

endmodule

module full_adder(output sum, output cout, input in1, in2, input cin);
wire w1, w2, w3;

xor(w1, in1, in2);
xor(sum, w1, cin);
and(w2, w1, cin);
and(w3, in1, in2);
or(cout, w2, w3);

endmodule

module full_adder(output sum, output cout, input in1, in2, input cin);
wire w1, w2, w3;

and(w2, w1, cin);
and(w3, in1, in2);
or(cout, w2, w3);

module full_adder(output sum, output cout, input in1, in2, input cin);
wire w1, w2, w3;

xor(w1, in1, in2);
xor(sum, w1, cin);
and(w2, w1, cin);
and(w3, in1, in2);
or(cout, w2, w3);

//Design a 4-bit adder.
//There are two 4 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The adder should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to determine the output sum and cout.
//Please finish the module.

module adder(output [3:0] sum, output cout, input [3:0] in1, in2, input cin);
wire [3:0] in1, in2;
wire cin;
wire [3:0] sum;
wire cout;

assign in1 = in1;
assign in2 = in2;
assign cin = cin;

assign sum = sum;
assign cout = cout;

endmodule

//Design a 4-bit adder.
//There are two 4 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The adder should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to determine the output sum and cout.
//Please finish the module.

module adder(output [3:0] sum, output cout, input [3:0] in1, in2, input cin);
wire [3:0] in1_wire, in2_wire;
wire cin_wire;

assign in1_wire = in1;
assign in2_wire = in2;
assign cin_wire = cin;

full_adder FA1(sum[0], in1_wire[0], in2_wire[0], cin_wire, cout_wire);
full_adder FA2(sum[1], in1_wire[1], in2_wire[1], cout_wire, cout_wire);
full_adder FA3(sum[2], in1_wire[2], in2_wire[2], cout_wire, cout_wire);
full_adder FA4(sum[3], in1_wire[3], in2_wire[3], cout_wire, cout_wire);

endmodule

//Design a 4-bit adder.
//There are two 4 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The adder should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to determine the output sum and cout.
//Please finish the module.

module adder(output [3:0] sum, output cout, input [3:0] in1, in2, input cin);
wire [3:0] in1_wire, in2_wire;
wire cin_wire;

assign in1_wire = in1;
assign in2_wire = in2;
assign cin_wire = cin;

full_adder FA1(sum[0], in1_wire[0], in2_wire[0], cin_wire, cout_wire);
full_adder FA2(sum[1], in1_wire[1], in2_wire[1], cout_wire, cout_wire);
full_adder FA3(sum[2], in1_wire[2], in2_wire[2], cout_wire, cout_wire);
full_adder FA4(sum[3], in1_wire[3], in2_wire[3], cout_wire, cout_wire);

endmodule

module full_adder(output sum, output cout, input in1, in2, input cin);
wire w1, w2, w3;

xor(w1, in1, in2);
xor(sum, w1, cin);
and(w2, w1, cin);
and(w3, in1, in2);
or(cout, w2, w3);

endmodule

//Design a 4-bit adder.
//There are two 4 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The adder should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to determine the output sum and cout.
//Please finish the module.

module adder(output [3:0] sum, output cout, input [3:0] in1, in2, input cin);
wire [3:0] in1_wire, in2_wire;
wire cin_wire;

assign in1_wire = in1;
assign in2_wire = in2;
assign cin_wire = cin;

full_adder FA1(sum[0], in1_wire[0], in2_wire[0], cin_wire, cout_wire);
full_adder FA2(sum[1], in1_wire[1], in2_wire[1], cout_wire, cout_wire);
full_adder FA3(sum[2], in1_wire[2], in2_wire[2], cout_wire, cout_wire);
full_adder FA4(sum[3], in1_wire[3], in2_wire[3], cout_wire, cout_wire);

endmodule

//Design a 4-bit adder.
//There are two 4 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The adder should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to determine the output sum and cout.
//Please finish the module.

module adder(output [3:0] sum, output cout, input [3:0] in1, in2, input cin);
wire [3:0] in1_wire, in2_wire;
wire cin_wire;

assign in1_wire = in1;
assign in2_wire = in2;
assign cin_wire = cin;

full_adder FA1(sum[0], in1_wire[0], in2_wire[0], cin_wire, cout_wire);
full_adder FA2(sum[1], in1_wire[1], in2_wire[1], cout_wire, cout_wire);
full_adder FA3(sum[2], in1_wire[2], in2_wire[2], cout_wire, cout_wire);
full_adder FA4(sum[3], in1_wire[3], in2_wire[3], cout_wire, cout_wire);

endmodule

module full_adder(output sum, output cout, input in1, in2, input cin);
wire w1, w2, w3;

xor(w1, in1, in2);
xor(sum, w1, cin);
and(w2, w1, cin);
and(w3, in1, in2);
or(cout, w2, w3);

endmodule

module fa(output sum, output cout, input a, b, cin);
wire c1, c2, c3;

xor(sum, a, b, cin);
and(c1, a, b);
and(c2, b, cin);
and(c3, a, cin);
or(cout, c1, c2, c3);

endmodule

//Design a 4-bit adder.
//There are two 4 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The adder should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to determine the output sum and cout.
//Please finish the module.

module adder(output [3:0] sum, output cout, input [3:0] in1, in2, input cin);
wire c1, c2, c3;

full_adder FA1(sum[0], c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);
full_adder FA2(sum[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
full_adder FA3(sum[2], c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);
full_adder FA4(sum[3], cout, in1[3], in2[3], c3);

endmodule

module full_adder(output sum, output cout, input in1, in2, cin);
wire x, y, z;

xor(sum, in1, in2, cin);
and(x, in1, in2);
and(y, in1, cin);
and(z, in2, cin);
or(cout, x, y, z);

endmodule

//Design a 4-bit adder.
//There are two 4 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The adder should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to determine the output sum and cout.
//Please finish the module.

module adder(output [3:0] sum, output cout, input [3:0] in1, in2, input cin);
wire [3:0] in1_wire, in2_wire;
wire cin_wire;

assign in1_wire = in1;
assign in2_wire = in2;
assign cin_wire = cin;

full_adder FA1(sum[0], in1_wire[0], in2_wire[0], cin_wire, cout_wire);
full_adder FA2(sum[1], in1_wire[1], in2_wire[1], cout_wire, cout_wire);
full_adder FA3(sum[2], in1_wire[2], in2_wire[2], cout_wire, cout_wire);
full_adder FA4(sum[3], in1_wire[3], in2_wire[3], cout_wire, cout_wire);

endmodule

//Design a 4-bit adder.
//There are two 4 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The adder should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to determine the output sum and cout.
//Please finish the module.

assign in2_wire = in2;
assign cin_wire = cin;

full_adder FA3(sum[2], in1_wire[2], in2_wire[2], cout_wire, cout_wire);
full_adder FA4(sum[3], in1_wire[3], in2_wire[3], cout_wire, cout_wire);

module full_adder(output sum, output cout, input in1, in2, input cin);
wire w1, w2, w3;

xor(w1, in1, in2);
xor(sum, w1, cin);
and(w2, w1, cin);
and(w3, in1, in2);
or(cout, w2, w3);

endmodule

//Design a 4-bit adder.
//There are two 4 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The adder should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to determine the output sum and cout.
//Please finish the module.

module adder(output [3:0] sum, output cout, input [3:0] in1, in2, input cin);
wire [3:0] in1_wire, in2_wire;
wire cin_wire;

assign in1_wire = in1;
assign in2_wire = in2;
assign cin_wire = cin;

full_adder FA1(sum[0], in1_wire[0], in2_wire[0], cin_wire, cout_wire);
full_adder FA2(sum[1], in1_wire[1], in2_wire[1], cout_wire, cout_wire);
full_adder FA3(sum[2], in1_wire[2], in2_wire[2], cout_wire, cout_wire);
full_adder FA4(sum[3], in1_wire[3], in2_wire[3], cout_wire, cout_wire);

endmodule

module full_adder(output sum, output cout, input in1, in2, input cin);
wire w1, w2, w3;

xor(w1, in1, in2);
xor(sum, w1, cin);
and(w2, w1, cin);
and(w3, in1, in2);
or(cout, w2, w3);

endmodule

//Design a 4-bit adder.
//There are two 4 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The adder should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to determine the output sum and cout.
//Please finish the module.

module adder(output [3:0] sum, output cout, input [3:0] in1, in2, input cin);
wire [3:0] in1_wire, in2_wire;
wire cin_wire;

assign in1_wire = in1;
assign in2_wire = in2;
assign cin_wire = cin;

full_adder FA1(sum[0], in1_wire[0], in2_wire[0], cin_wire, cout_wire);
full_adder FA2(sum[1], in1_wire[1], in2_wire[1], cout_wire, cout_wire);
full_adder FA3(sum[2], in1_wire[2], in2_wire[2], cout_wire, cout_wire);
full_adder FA4(sum[3], in1_wire[3], in2_wire[3], cout_wire, cout_wire);

endmodule

module full_adder(output sum, output cout, input in1, in2, input cin);
wire w1, w2, w3;

xor(w1, in1, in2);
xor(sum, w1, cin);
and(w2, w1, cin);
and(w3, in1, in2);
or(cout, w2, w3);

endmodule

//Design a 4-bit adder.
//There are two 4 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The adder should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to determine the output sum and cout.
//Please finish the module.

module adder(output [3:0] sum, output cout, input [3:0] in1, in2, input cin);
wire [3:0] in1_wire, in2_wire;
wire cin_wire;

assign in1_wire = in1;
assign in2_wire = in2;
assign cin_wire = cin;

full_adder FA1(sum[0], in1_wire[0], in2_wire[0], cin_wire, cout_wire);
full_adder FA2(sum[1], in1_wire[1], in2_wire[1], cout_wire, cout_wire);
full_adder FA3(sum[2], in1_wire[2], in2_wire[2], cout_wire, cout_wire);
full_adder FA4(sum[3], in1_wire[3], in2_wire[3], cout_wire, cout_wire);

endmodule

module full_adder(output sum, output cout, input in1, in2, input cin);
wire w1, w2, w3;

xor(w1, in1, in2);
xor(sum, w1, cin);
and(w2, w1, cin);
and(w3, in1, in2);
or(cout, w2, w3);

endmodule

//There are two 4 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.

module adder(output [3:0] sum, output cout, input [3:0] in1, in2, input cin);

wire [3:0] in2_wire;
wire cin_wire;

assign cin_wire = cin;

module full_adder(output sum, carry, input a, b, cin);
wire a_wire, b_wire, c_wire;

assign a_wire = a;
assign b_wire = b;

//Design a 4-bit adder.
//There are two 4 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.

module adder(output [3:0] sum, output cout, input [3:0] in1, in2, input cin);
wire [3:0] in1_wire;
wire [3:0] in2_wire;
wire cin_wire;

assign in2_wire = in2;
assign cin_wire = cin;

module full_adder(output sum, carry, input a, b, cin);
wire a_wire, b_wire, c_wire;

assign a_wire = a;
assign b_wire = b;
assign c_wire = cin;

half_adder HA1(sum, c1, a_wire, b_wire);
half_adder HA2(sum, c2, c1, c_wire);

assign carry = c2;

endmodule

module half_adder(output sum, carry, input a, b);
wire a_wire, b_wire;

assign a_wire = a;
assign b_wire = b;

xor(sum, a_wire, b_wire);
and(carry, a_wire, b_wire);

endmodule

//Design a 4-bit adder.
//There are two 4 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The adder should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to determine the output sum and cout.
//Please finish the module.

module adder(output [3:0] sum, output cout, input [3:0] in1, in2, input cin);
wire [3:0] in1_wire, in2_wire;
wire cin_wire;

assign in1_wire = in1;
assign in2_wire = in2;
assign cin_wire = cin;

module full_adder(output sum, output cout, input in1, in2, input cin);
wire w1, w2, w3;

xor(w1, in1, in2);
xor(sum, w1, cin);
and(w2, w1, cin);
and(w3, in1, in2);
or(cout, w2, w3);

endmodule

//Design a 4-bit adder.
//There are two 4 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The adder should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to determine the output sum and cout.
//Please finish the module.

module adder(output [3:0] sum, output cout, input [3:0] in1, in2, input cin);
wire [3:0] in1_wire, in2_wire;
wire cin_wire;

assign in1_wire = in1;
assign in2_wire = in2;
assign cin_wire = cin;

full_adder FA1(sum[0], in1_wire[0], in2_wire[0], cin_wire, cout_wire);
full_adder FA2(sum[1], in1_wire[1], in2_wire[1], cout_wire, cout_wire);
full_adder FA3(sum[2], in1_wire[2], in2_wire[2], cout_wire, cout_wire);
full_adder FA4(sum[3], in1_wire[3], in2_wire[3], cout_wire, cout_wire);

endmodule

//Design a 4-bit adder.
//There are two 4 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The adder should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to determine the output sum and cout.
//Please finish the module.

module adder(output [3:0] sum, output cout, input [3:0] in1, in2, input cin);
wire [3:0] in1_wire, in2_wire;
wire cin_wire;

assign in1_wire = in1;
assign in2_wire = in2;
assign cin_wire = cin;

full_adder FA1(sum[0], in1_wire[0], in2_wire[0], cin_wire, cout_wire);
full_adder FA2(sum[1], in1_wire[1], in2_wire[1], cout_wire, cout_wire);
full_adder FA3(sum[2], in1_wire[2], in2_wire[2], cout_wire, cout_wire);
full_adder FA4(sum[3], in1_wire[3], in2_wire[3], cout_wire, cout_wire);

endmodule

module full_adder(output sum, output cout, input in1, in2, input cin);
wire w1, w2, w3;

xor(w1, in1, in2);
xor(sum, w1, cin);
and(w2, w1, cin);
and(w3, in1, in2);
or(cout, w2, w3);

endmodule

wire [3:0] in1_wire, in2_wire;

assign cin_wire = cin;

module full_adder(output sum, output cout, input in1, in2, input cin);
wire w1, w2, w3;

xor(w1, in1, in2);
xor(sum, w1, cin);
and(w2, w1, cin);
and(w3, in1, in2);
or(cout, w2, w3);

//Design a 4-bit adder.
//There are two 4 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The adder should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to determine the output sum and cout.
//Please finish the module.

module adder(output [3:0] sum, output cout, input [3:0] in1, in2, input cin);
wire [3:0] in1_wire, in2_wire;
wire cin_wire;

assign in1_wire = in1;
assign in2_wire = in2;
assign cin_wire = cin;

full_adder FA1(sum[0], in1_wire[0], in2_wire[0], cin_wire, cout_wire);
full_adder FA2(sum[1], in1_wire[1], in2_wire[1], cout_wire, cout_wire);
full_adder FA3(sum[2], in1_wire[2], in2_wire[2], cout_wire, cout_wire);
full_adder FA4(sum[3], in1_wire[3], in2_wire[3], cout_wire, cout_wire);

endmodule

//Design a 4-bit adder.
//There are two 4 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The adder should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to determine the output sum and cout.
//Please finish the module.

module adder(output [3:0] sum, output cout, input [3:0] in1, in2, input cin);
wire [3:0] in1_wire, in2_wire;
wire cin_wire;

assign in1_wire = in1;
assign in2_wire = in2;
assign cin_wire = cin;

full_adder FA1(sum[0], in1_wire[0], in2_wire[0], cin_wire, cout_wire);
full_adder FA2(sum[1], in1_wire[1], in2_wire[1], cout_wire, cout_wire);
full_adder FA3(sum[2], in1_wire[2], in2_wire[2], cout_wire, cout_wire);
full_adder FA4(sum[3], in1_wire[3], in2_wire[3], cout_wire, cout_wire);

endmodule

module full_adder(output sum, output cout, input in1, in2, input cin);
wire w1, w2, w3;

xor(w1, in1, in2);
xor(sum, w1, cin);
and(w2, w1, cin);
and(w3, in1, in2);
or(cout, w2, w3);

endmodule

//Design a 4-bit adder.
//There are two 4 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The adder should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to determine the output sum and cout.
//Please finish the module.

module adder(output [3:0] sum, output cout, input [3:0] in1, in2, input cin);
wire [3:0] in1_wire, in2_wire;
wire cin_wire;

assign in1_wire = in1;
assign in2_wire = in2;
assign cin_wire = cin;

full_adder FA1(sum[0], in1_wire[0], in2_wire[0], cin_wire, cout_wire);
full_adder FA2(sum[1], in1_wire[1], in2_wire[1], cout_wire, cout_wire);
full_adder FA3(sum[2], in1_wire[2], in2_wire[2], cout_wire, cout_wire);

//Design a 4-bit adder.
//There are two 4 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The adder should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to determine the output sum and cout.
//Please finish the module.

module adder(output [3:0] sum, output cout, input [3:0] in1, in2, input cin);
wire [3:0] in1_wire, in2_wire;
wire cin_wire;

assign in1_wire = in1;
assign in2_wire = in2;
assign cin_wire = cin;

full_adder FA1(sum[0], in1_wire[0], in2_wire[0], cin_wire, cout_wire);
full_adder FA2(sum[1], in1_wire[1], in2_wire[1], cout_wire, cout_wire);
full_adder FA3(sum[2], in1_wire[2], in2_wire[2], cout_wire, cout_wire);
full_adder FA4(sum[3], in1_wire[3], in2_wire[3], cout_wire, cout_wire);

endmodule

module full_adder(output sum, output cout, input in1, in2, input cin);
wire w1, w2, w3;

xor(w1, in1, in2);
xor(sum, w1, cin);
and(w2, w1, cin);
and(w3, in1, in2);
or(cout, w2, w3);

endmodule

//There are two 4 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The adder should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to determine the output sum and cout.
//Please finish the module.

module adder(output [3:0] sum, output cout, input [3:0] in1, in2, input cin);
wire [3:0] in1_wire, in2_wire;
wire cin_wire;

assign in1_wire = in1;
assign in2_wire = in2;
assign cin_wire = cin;

module full_adder(output sum, output cout, input in1, in2, input cin);
wire w1, w2, w3;

xor(w1, in1, in2);
xor(sum, w1, cin);
and(w2, w1, cin);
and(w3, in1, in2);
or(cout, w2, w3);

endmodule

//Design a 4-bit adder.
//There are two 4 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The adder should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to determine the output sum and cout.
//Please finish the module.

module adder(output [3:0] sum, output cout, input [3:0] in1, in2, input cin);
wire [3:0] in1_wire, in2_wire;
wire cin_wire;

assign in1_wire = in1;
assign in2_wire = in2;
assign cin_wire = cin;

full_adder FA1(sum[0], in1_wire[0], in2_wire[0], cin_wire, cout_wire);
full_adder FA2(sum[1], in1_wire[1], in2_wire[1], cout_wire, cout_wire);
full_adder FA3(sum[2], in1_wire[2], in2_wire[2], cout_wire, cout_wire);
full_adder FA4(sum[3], in1_wire[3], in2_wire[3], cout_wire, cout_wire);

endmodule

//Design a 4-bit adder.
//There are two 4 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The adder should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to determine the output sum and cout.
//Please finish the module.

module adder(output [3:0] sum, output cout, input [3:0] in1, in2, input cin);
wire [3:0] in1_wire, in2_wire;
wire cin_wire;

assign in1_wire = in1;
assign in2_wire = in2;
assign cin_wire = cin;

full_adder FA1(sum[0], in1_wire[0], in2_wire[0], cin_wire, cout_wire);
full_adder FA2(sum[1], in1_wire[1], in2_wire[1], cout_wire, cout_wire);
full_adder FA3(sum[2], in1_wire[2], in2_wire[2], cout_wire, cout_wire);
full_adder FA4(sum[3], in1_wire[3], in2_wire[3], cout_wire, cout_wire);

endmodule

module full_adder(output sum, output cout, input in1, in2, input cin);
wire w1, w2, w3;

xor(w1, in1, in2);
xor(sum, w1, cin);
and(w2, w1, cin);
and(w3, in1, in2);
or(cout, w2, w3);

endmodule

assign cin_wire = cin;

module full_adder(output sum, output cout, input in1, in2, input cin);
wire w1, w2, w3;

xor(w1, in1, in2);
xor(sum, w1, cin);
and(w2, w1, cin);
and(w3, in1, in2);
or(cout, w2, w3);

endmodule

//Design a 4-bit adder.
//There are two 4 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The adder should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to determine the output sum and cout.
//Please finish the module.

module adder(output [3:0] sum, output cout, input [3:0] in1, in2, input cin);
wire [3:0] in1_wire, in2_wire;
wire cin_wire;

assign in1_wire = in1;
assign in2_wire = in2;
assign cin_wire = cin;

full_adder FA1(sum[0], in1_wire[0], in2_wire[0], cin_wire, cout_wire);
full_adder FA2(sum[1], in1_wire[1], in2_wire[1], cout_wire, cout_wire);
full_adder FA3(sum[2], in1_wire[2], in2_wire[2], cout_wire, cout_wire);
full_adder FA4(sum[3], in1_wire[3], in2_wire[3], cout_wire, cout_wire);

endmodule

//Design a 4-bit adder.
//There are two 4 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The adder should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to determine the output sum and cout.
//Please finish the module.

module adder(output [3:0] sum, output cout, input [3:0] in1, in2, input cin);
wire [3:0] in1_wire, in2_wire;
wire cin_wire;

assign in1_wire = in1;
assign in2_wire = in2;
assign cin_wire = cin;

full_adder FA1(sum[0], in1_wire[0], in2_wire[0], cin_wire, cout_wire);
full_adder FA2(sum[1], in1_wire[1], in2_wire[1], cout_wire, cout_wire);
full_adder FA3(sum[2], in1_wire[2], in2_wire[2], cout_wire, cout_wire);
full_adder FA4(sum[3], in1_wire[3], in2_wire[3], cout_wire, cout_wire);

endmodule

module full_adder(output sum, output cout, input in1, in2, input cin);
wire w1, w2, w3;

xor(w1, in1, in2);
xor(sum, w1, cin);
and(w2, w1, cin);
and(w3, in1, in2);
or(cout, w2, w3);

endmodule

module full_adder(output sum, output cout, input in1, in2, input cin);
wire w1, w2, w3;

xor(w1, in1, in2);
xor(sum, w1, cin);
and(w2, w1, cin);
and(w3, in1, in2);
or(cout, w2, w3);

endmodule

//Design a 4-bit adder.
//There are two 4 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The adder should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to determine the output sum and cout.
//Please finish the module.

module adder(output [3:0] sum, output cout, input [3:0] in1, in2, input cin);
wire [3:0] in1_wire, in2_wire;
wire cin_wire;
wire [3:0] sum_wire;
wire cout_wire;

assign in1_wire = in1;
assign in2_wire = in2;
assign cin_wire = cin;

full_adder FA1(sum_wire[0], c1, in1_wire[0], in2_wire[0], cin_wire);
full_adder FA2(sum_wire[1], c2, in1_wire[1], in2_wire[1], c1);
full_adder FA3(sum_wire[2], c3, in1_wire[2], in2_wire[2], c2);
full_adder FA4(sum_wire[3], cout_wire, in1_wire[3], in2_wire[3], c3);

endmodule

//Design a 4-bit adder.

wire cin_wire;
wire [3:0] sum_wire;

module full_adder(output wire sum,
                  output wire cout,
                  input wire in1,
                  input wire in2,
                  input wire cin);

wire temp1;
wire temp2;
wire temp3;

xor(sum, in1, in2, cin);
and(temp1,in1,in2);
and(temp2,in1,cin);
and(temp3,in2,cin);
or(cout,temp1,temp2,temp3);

endmodule

//There are two 4 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.

//The adder should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to determine the output sum and cout.

module fulladder(output sum, carry, input a, b, cin);
wire c1,c2,c3;

xor(sum,a,b,cin);
and(c1,a,b);
and(c2,b,cin);
and(c3,a,cin);
or(carry,c1,c2,c3);

endmodule

//Design a 4-bit adder.
//There are two 4 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The adder should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to determine the output sum and cout.
//Please finish the module.

module adder(output [3:0] sum, output cout, input [3:0] in1, in2, input cin);
wire [3:0] in1_wire, in2_wire;
wire cin_wire;

assign in1_wire = in1;
assign in2_wire = in2;
assign cin_wire = cin;

full_adder FA1(sum[0], in1_wire[0], in2_wire[0], cin_wire, cout_wire);
full_adder FA2(sum[1], in1_wire[1], in2_wire[1], cout_wire, cout_wire);
full_adder FA3(sum[2], in1_wire[2], in2_wire[2], cout_wire, cout_wire);
full_adder FA4(sum[3], in1_wire[3], in2_wire[3], cout_wire, cout_wire);

endmodule

//Design a 4-bit adder.
//There are two 4 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The adder should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to determine the output sum and cout.
//Please finish the module.

module adder(output [3:0] sum, output cout, input [3:0] in1, in2, input cin);
wire [3:0] in1_wire, in2_wire;
wire cin_wire;

assign in1_wire = in1;
assign in2_wire = in2;
assign cin_wire = cin;

full_adder FA1(sum[0], in1_wire[0], in2_wire[0], cin_wire, cout_wire);
full_adder FA2(sum[1], in1_wire[1], in2_wire[1], cout_wire, cout_wire);
full_adder FA3(sum[2], in1_wire[2], in2_wire[2], cout_wire, cout_wire);
full_adder FA4(sum[3], in1_wire[3], in2_wire[3], cout_wire, cout_wire);

endmodule

module full_adder(output sum, output cout, input in1, in2, input cin);
wire w1, w2, w3;

xor(w1, in1, in2);
xor(sum, w1, cin);
and(w2, w1, cin);
and(w3, in1, in2);
or(cout, w2, w3);

endmodule

//Design a 4-bit adder.
//There are two 4 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The adder should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to determine the output sum and cout.
//Please finish the module.

module adder(output [3:0] sum, output cout, input [3:0] in1, in2, input cin);
wire [3:0] in1_wire, in2_wire;
wire cin_wire;

assign in1_wire = in1;
assign in2_wire = in2;
assign cin_wire = cin;

full_adder FA1(sum[0], in1_wire[0], in2_wire[0], cin_wire, cout_wire);
full_adder FA2(sum[1], in1_wire[1], in2_wire[1], cout_wire, cout_wire);
full_adder FA3(sum[2], in1_wire[2], in2_wire[2], cout_wire, cout_wire);
full_adder FA4(sum[3], in1_wire[3], in2_wire[3], cout_wire, cout_wire);

endmodule

//Design a 4-bit adder.
//There are two 4 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The adder should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to determine the output sum and cout.
//Please finish the module.

module adder(output [3:0] sum, output cout, input [3:0] in1, in2, input cin);
wire [3:0] in1_wire, in2_wire;
wire cin_wire;

assign in1_wire = in1;
assign in2_wire = in2;
assign cin_wire = cin;

full_adder FA1(sum[0], in1_wire[0], in2_wire[0], cin_wire, cout_wire);
full_adder FA2(sum[1], in1_wire[1], in2_wire[1], cout_wire, cout_wire);
full_adder FA3(sum[2], in1_wire[2], in2_wire[2], cout_wire, cout_wire);
full_adder FA4(sum[3], in1_wire[3], in2_wire[3], cout_wire, cout_wire);

endmodule

module full_adder(output sum, output cout, input in1, in2, input cin);
wire w1, w2, w3;

xor(w1, in1, in2);
xor(sum, w1, cin);
and(w2, w1, cin);
and(w3, in1, in2);
or(cout, w2, w3);

endmodule

//Design a 4-bit adder.
//There are two 4 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The adder should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to determine the output sum and cout.
//Please finish the module.

module adder(output [3:0] sum, output cout, input [3:0] in1, in2, input cin);
wire [3:0] in1_wire, in2_wire;
wire cin_wire;

assign in1_wire = in1;
assign in2_wire = in2;
assign cin_wire = cin;

full_adder FA1(sum[0], in1_wire[0], in2_wire[0], cin_wire, cout_wire);
full_adder FA2(sum[1], in1_wire[1], in2_wire[1], cout_wire, cout_wire);
full_adder FA3(sum[2], in1_wire[2], in2_wire[2], cout_wire, cout_wire);
full_adder FA4(sum[3], in1_wire[3], in2_wire[3], cout_wire, cout_wire);

endmodule

//There are two 4 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The adder should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to determine the output sum and cout.
//Please finish the module.

wire cin_wire;

assign in1_wire = in1;
assign in2_wire = in2;
assign cin_wire = cin;

full_adder FA4(sum[3], in1_wire[3], in2_wire[3], cout_wire, cout_wire);

module full_adder(output sum, output cout, input in1, in2, input cin);
wire w1, w2, w3;

xor(w1, in1, in2);
xor(sum, w1, cin);
and(w2, w1, cin);
and(w3, in1, in2);
or(cout, w2, w3);

endmodule

//Design a 4-bit adder.
//There are two 4 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The adder should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to determine the output sum and cout.
//Please finish the module.

//Design a 4-bit adder.
//There are two 4 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The adder should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to determine the output sum and cout.
//Please finish the module.

module adder(output [3:0] sum, output cout, input [3:0] in1, in2, input cin);
wire [3:0] in1_wire, in2_wire;
wire cin_wire;

assign in1_wire = in1;
assign in2_wire = in2;
assign cin_wire = cin;

full_adder FA1(sum[0], in1_wire[0], in2_wire[0], cin_wire, cout_wire);
full_adder FA2(sum[1], in1_wire[1], in2_wire[1], cout_wire, cout_wire);

//Design a 4-bit adder.
//There are two 4 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The adder should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to determine the output sum and cout.
//Please finish the module.

module adder(output [3:0] sum, output cout, input [3:0] in1, in2, input cin);
wire [3:0] in1_wire, in2_wire;
wire cin_wire;

assign in1_wire = in1;
assign in2_wire = in2;
assign cin_wire = cin;

full_adder FA1(sum[0], in1_wire[0], in2_wire[0], cin_wire, cout_wire);
full_adder FA2(sum[1], in1_wire[1], in2_wire[1], cout_wire, cout_wire);
full_adder FA3(sum[2], in1_wire[2], in2_wire[2], cout_wire, cout_wire);
full_adder FA4(sum[3], in1_wire[3], in2_wire[3], cout_wire, cout_wire);

endmodule

module full_adder(output sum, output cout, input in1, in2, input cin);
wire w1, w2, w3;

xor(w1, in1, in2);
xor(sum, w1, cin);
and(w2, w1, cin);
and(w3, in1, in2);
or(cout, w2, w3);

endmodule

//Design a 4-bit adder.
//There are two 4 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The adder should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to determine the output sum and cout.
//Please finish the module.

module adder(output [3:0] sum, output cout, input [3:0] in1, in2, input cin);
wire [3:0] in1_wire, in2_wire;
wire cin_wire;

assign in1_wire = in1;
assign in2_wire = in2;
assign cin_wire = cin;

full_adder FA1(sum[0], in1_wire[0], in2_wire[0], cin_wire, cout_wire);
full_adder FA2(sum[1], in1_wire[1], in2_wire[1], cout_wire, cout_wire);
full_adder FA3(sum[2], in1_wire[2], in2_wire[2], cout_wire, cout_wire);
full_adder FA4(sum[3], in1_wire[3], in2_wire[3], cout_wire, cout_wire);

endmodule

//Design a 4-bit adder.
//There are two 4 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The adder should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to determine the output sum and cout.
//Please finish the module.

module adder(output [3:0] sum, output cout, input [3:0] in1, in2, input cin);
wire [3:0] in1_wire, in2_wire;
wire cin_wire;

assign in1_wire = in1;
assign in2_wire = in2;
assign cin_wire = cin;

full_adder FA1(sum[0], in1_wire[0], in2_wire[0], cin_wire, cout_wire);
full_adder FA2(sum[1], in1_wire[1], in2_wire[1], cout_wire, cout_wire);
full_adder FA3(sum[2], in1_wire[2], in2_wire[2], cout_wire, cout_wire);
full_adder FA4(sum[3], in1_wire[3], in2_wire[3], cout_wire, cout_wire);

endmodule

module full_adder(output sum, output cout, input in1, in2, input cin);
wire w1, w2, w3;

xor(w1, in1, in2);
xor(sum, w1, cin);
and(w2, w1, cin);
and(w3, in1, in2);
or(cout, w2, w3);

endmodule

//Design a 4-bit adder.
//There are two 4 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The adder should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to determine the output sum and cout.
//Please finish the module.

module adder(output [3:0] sum, output cout, input [3:0] in1, in2, input cin);
wire [3:0] in1_wire, in2_wire;
wire cin_wire;

assign in1_wire = in1;
assign in2_wire = in2;
assign cin_wire = cin;

full_adder FA1(sum[0], in1_wire[0], in2_wire[0], cin_wire, cout_wire);
full_adder FA2(sum[1], in1_wire[1], in2_wire[1], cout_wire, cout_wire);
full_adder FA3(sum[2], in1_wire[2], in2_wire[2], cout_wire, cout_wire);
full_adder FA4(sum[3], in1_wire[3], in2_wire[3], cout_wire, cout_wire);

endmodule

//Design a 4-bit adder.
//There are two 4 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The adder should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to determine the output sum and cout.
//Please finish the module.

module adder(output [3:0] sum, output cout, input [3:0] in1, in2, input cin);
wire [3:0] in1_wire, in2_wire;
wire cin_wire;

assign in1_wire = in1;
assign in2_wire = in2;
assign cin_wire = cin;

full_adder FA1(sum[0], in1_wire[0], in2_wire[0], cin_wire, cout_wire);
full_adder FA2(sum[1], in1_wire[1], in2_wire[1], cout_wire, cout_wire);
full_adder FA3(sum[2], in1_wire[2], in2_wire[2], cout_wire, cout_wire);
full_adder FA4(sum[3], in1_wire[3], in2_wire[3], cout_wire, cout_wire);

endmodule

module full_adder(output sum, output cout, input in1, in2, input cin);
wire w1, w2, w3;

xor(w1, in1, in2);
xor(sum, w1, cin);
and(w2, w1, cin);
and(w3, in1, in2);
or(cout, w2, w3);

endmodule

//Design a 4-bit adder.
//There are two 4 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The adder should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to determine the output sum and cout.
//Please finish the module.

module adder(output [3:0] sum, output cout, input [3:0] in1, in2, input cin);
wire [3:0] in1_wire, in2_wire;
wire cin_wire;

assign in1_wire = in1;
assign in2_wire = in2;
assign cin_wire = cin;

full_adder FA1(sum[0], in1_wire[0], in2_wire[0], cin_wire, cout_wire);
full_adder FA2(sum[1], in1_wire[1], in2_wire[1], cout_wire, cout_wire);
full_adder FA3(sum[2], in1_wire[2], in2_wire[2], cout_wire, cout_wire);

module full_adder(output sum, output cout, input in1, in2, input cin);
wire w1, w2, w3;

xor(w1, in1, in2);
xor(sum, w1, cin);
and(w2, w1, cin);
and(w3, in1, in2);
or(cout, w2, w3);

endmodule

//Design a 4-bit adder.
//There are two 4 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The adder should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to determine the output sum and cout.
//Please finish the module.

module adder(output [3:0] sum, output cout, input [3:0] in1, in2, input cin);
wire [3:0] in1_wire, in2_wire;
wire cin_wire;

assign in1_wire = in1;
assign in2_wire = in2;
assign cin_wire = cin;

full_adder FA1(sum[0], in1_wire[0], in2_wire[0], cin_wire, cout_wire);
full_adder FA2(sum[1], in1_wire[1], in2_wire[1], cout_wire, cout_wire);
full_adder FA3(sum[2], in1_wire[2], in2_wire[2], cout_wire, cout_wire);
full_adder FA4(sum[3], in1_wire[3], in2_wire[3], cout_wire, cout_wire);

endmodule

module full_adder(output sum, output cout, input in1, in2, input cin);
wire w1, w2, w3;

xor(w1, in1, in2);
xor(sum, w1, cin);
and(w2, w1, cin);
and(w3, in1, in2);
or(cout, w2, w3);

endmodule

//There are two 4 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The adder should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to determine the output sum and cout.

//Design a 4-bit adder.
//There are two 4 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The adder should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to determine the output sum and cout.
//Please finish the module.

module adder(output [3:0] sum, output cout, input [3:0] in1, in2, input cin);
wire [3:0] c;

assign c[0] = cin;

full_adder FA0(sum[0], c[1], in1[0], in2[0], c[0]);
full_adder FA1(sum[1], c[2], in1[1], in2[1], c[1]);
full_adder FA2(sum[2], c[3], in1[2], in2[2], c[2]);
full_adder FA3(sum[3], cout, in1[3], in2[3], c[3]);

endmodule

module full_adder(output sum, output cout, input in1, in2, cin);
wire x, y, z;

xor(sum, in1, in2, cin);
and(x, in1, in2);
and(y, in1, cin);
and(z, in2, cin);
or(cout, x, y, z);

endmodule

//Design a 4-bit adder.
//There are two 4 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The adder should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to determine the output sum and cout.
//Please finish the module.

module adder(output [3:0] sum, output cout, input [3:0] in1, in2, input cin);
wire [3:0] in1_wire, in2_wire;
wire cin_wire;

assign in1_wire = in1;
assign in2_wire = in2;

//Design a 4-bit adder.
//There are two 4 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The adder should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to determine the output sum and cout.
//Please finish the module.

module adder(output [3:0] sum, output cout, input [3:0] in1, in2, input cin);
wire [3:0] in1_wire, in2_wire;
wire cin_wire;

assign in1_wire = in1;
assign in2_wire = in2;
assign cin_wire = cin;

full_adder FA1(sum[0], in1_wire[0], in2_wire[0], cin_wire, cout_wire);
full_adder FA2(sum[1], in1_wire[1], in2_wire[1], cout_wire, cout_wire);
full_adder FA3(sum[2], in1_wire[2], in2_wire[2], cout_wire, cout_wire);
full_adder FA4(sum[3], in1_wire[3], in2_wire[3], cout_wire, cout_wire);

endmodule

module full_adder(output sum, output cout, input in1, in2, input cin);
wire w1, w2, w3;

xor(w1, in1, in2);
xor(sum, w1, cin);
and(w2, w1, cin);
and(w3, in1, in2);
or(cout, w2, w3);

endmodule

//Design a 4-bit adder.
//There are two 4 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The adder should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to determine the output sum and cout.
//Please finish the module.

module adder(output [3:0] sum, output cout, input [3:0] in1, in2, input cin);
wire [3:0] in1_wire, in2_wire;
wire cin_wire;

assign in1_wire = in1;
assign in2_wire = in2;
assign cin_wire = cin;

full_adder FA1(sum[0], in1_wire[0], in2_wire[0], cin_wire, cout_wire);
full_adder FA2(sum[1], in1_wire[1], in2_wire[1], cout_wire, cout_wire);
full_adder FA3(sum[2], in1_wire[2], in2_wire[2], cout_wire, cout_wire);
full_adder FA4(sum[3], in1_wire[3], in2_wire[3], cout_wire, cout_wire);

endmodule

module full_adder(output sum, output cout, input in1, in2, input cin);
wire w1, w2, w3;

xor(w1, in1, in2);
xor(sum, w1, cin);
and(w2, w1, cin);
and(w3, in1, in2);
or(cout, w2, w3);

endmodule

//Design a 4-bit adder.
//There are two 4 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The adder should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to determine the output sum and cout.
//Please finish the module.

module adder(output [3:0] sum, output cout, input [3:0] in1, in2, input cin);
wire [3:0] in1_wire, in2_wire;
wire cin_wire;

assign in1_wire = in1;
assign in2_wire = in2;
assign cin_wire = cin;

full_adder FA1(sum[0], in1_wire[0], in2_wire[0], cin_wire, cout_wire);
full_adder FA2(sum[1], in1_wire[1], in2_wire[1], cout_wire, cout_wire);
full_adder FA3(sum[2], in1_wire[2], in2_wire[2], cout_wire, cout_wire);
full_adder FA4(sum[3], in1_wire[3], in2_wire[3], cout_wire, cout_wire);

endmodule

//Design a 4-bit adder.
//There are two 4 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The adder should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to determine the output sum and cout.
//Please finish the module.

module adder(output [3:0] sum, output cout, input [3:0] in1, in2, input cin);
wire [3:0] in1_wire, in2_wire;
wire cin_wire;

assign in1_wire = in1;
assign in2_wire = in2;
assign cin_wire = cin;

full_adder FA1(sum[0], in1_wire[0], in2_wire[0], cin_wire, cout_wire);
full_adder FA2(sum[1], in1_wire[1], in2_wire[1], cout_wire, cout_wire);
full_adder FA3(sum[2], in1_wire[2], in2_wire[2], cout_wire, cout_wire);
full_adder FA4(sum[3], in1_wire[3], in2_wire[3], cout_wire, cout_wire);

endmodule

module full_adder(output sum, output cout, input in1, in2, input cin);
wire w1, w2, w3;

xor(w1, in1, in2);
xor(sum, w1, cin);
and(w2, w1, cin);
and(w3, in1, in2);
or(cout, w2, w3);

endmodule

//Design a 4-bit adder.
//There are two 4 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The adder should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to determine the output sum and cout.
//Please finish the module.

module adder(output [3:0] sum, output cout, input [3:0] in1, in2, input cin);
wire [3:0] in1_wire, in2_wire;
wire cin_wire;

assign in1_wire = in1;
assign in2_wire = in2;
assign cin_wire = cin;

full_adder FA1(sum[0], in1_wire[0], in2_wire[0], cin_wire, cout_wire);
full_adder FA2(sum[1], in1_wire[1], in2_wire[1], cout_wire, cout_wire);
full_adder FA3(sum[2], in1_wire[2], in2_wire[2], cout_wire, cout_wire);
full_adder FA4(sum[3], in1_wire[3], in2_wire[3], cout_wire, cout_wire);

endmodule

//Design a 4-bit adder.
//There are two 4 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The adder should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to determine the output sum and cout.
//Please finish the module.

module adder(output [3:0] sum, output cout, input [3:0] in1, in2, input cin);
wire [3:0] in1_wire, in2_wire;
wire cin_wire;

assign in1_wire = in1;
assign in2_wire = in2;
assign cin_wire = cin;

full_adder FA1(sum[0], in1_wire[0], in2_wire[0], cin_wire, cout_wire);
full_adder FA2(sum[1], in1_wire[1], in2_wire[1], cout_wire, cout_wire);
full_adder FA3(sum[2], in1_wire[2], in2_wire[2], cout_wire, cout_wire);
full_adder FA4(sum[3], in1_wire[3], in2_wire[3], cout_wire, cout_wire);

endmodule

module full_adder(output sum, output cout, input in1, in2, input cin);
wire w1, w2, w3;

xor(w1, in1, in2);
xor(sum, w1, cin);
and(w2, w1, cin);
and(w3, in1, in2);
or(cout, w2, w3);

endmodule

//Design a 4-bit adder.
//There are two 4 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The adder should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to determine the output sum and cout.
//Please finish the module.

module adder(output [3:0] sum, output cout, input [3:0] in1, in2, input cin);
wire [3:0] in1_wire, in2_wire;
wire cin_wire;

assign in1_wire = in1;
assign in2_wire = in2;
assign cin_wire = cin;

full_adder FA1(sum[0], in1_wire[0], in2_wire[0], cin_wire, cout_wire);
full_adder FA2(sum[1], in1_wire[1], in2_wire[1], cout_wire, cout_wire);
full_adder FA3(sum[2], in1_wire[2], in2_wire[2], cout_wire, cout_wire);
full_adder FA4(sum[3], in1_wire[3], in2_wire[3], cout_wire, cout_wire);

endmodule
